data.title: Dental Image Therapy Centres
data.meta_description: Our north Winnipeg dental clinic is located in Garden City Shopping Centre, use the southeast entrance next to Winners.
data.text:
Dr. Donald Dziewit

Dr. Donald Dziewit was born and raised in Winnipeg. He graduated from the Faculty of Dentistry at the University of Manitoba with a Doctorate of Dental Medicine in 1994. Dr. Dziewit enjoys being a general dentist and performs many different types of treatment, including replacing teeth with implants and changing smiles with LumineersÂ®. He has been a dentist with Dental Image Therapy Centres since 1998 and became a partner at the same location in 2007. When Dr. Dziewit is not spending time with his wife and children out at the lake, he enjoys golfing, reading and the art of BBQ.

Dr. Linda Simpson

Dr. Linda Simpson was raised in the town of Miami, Manitoba, but moved to Winnipeg to attend the University of Manitoba in 1996. Dr. Simpson graduated from the Faculty of Dentistry with a Doctorate in Dental Medicine and a Bachelor of Science in Dentistry in 2002. She joined Dental Image Therapy Centres the same year and became a partner at this location in 2007. When Dr. Simpson is not at work she enjoys spending time with her husband and four children. Their love of the outdoors keeps them busy gardening and biking.â

Dr. Mariam Nesseim

Dr. Mariam Nesseim was born in Egypt where she obtained her first dental degree and practised for a few years. She is also a graduate of the Faculty of Dentistry at the University of Manitoba with a Doctorate of Medical Dentistry. When Dr. Nesseim is not busy at her practice at Dental Image Therapy Centres, she enjoys travelling, reading, and spending time with family and friends. Dr. Nesseim is fluent in both English and Arabic.

Dr. Deji Omotayo

Dr. Deji Omotayo was born in Lagos, Nigeria. After receiving his first dental degree and practicing for 10 years in Nigeria, he moved to Canada in 2019. He then moved to Winnipeg and received his Doctor of Dental Medicine degree from the University of Manitoba. Dr. Deji enjoys meeting and interacting with people, which complements his patient-centered dental care. Outside work, he enjoys spending time with his wife and two sons, playing or watching soccer, and reading.

Dr. Roland DeBrouwere

Anesthesiologist

Dr. Roland DeBrouwere completed his Bachelor of Science and Doctor of Medicine in Dentistry from the University of Manitoba in 1985. After completing a hospital dentistry internship, Dr. DeBrouwere went on to complete a medical degree and residency in anesthesiology at the University of Manitoba, and a fellowship at the University of Toronto. Dr. DeBrouwere continues to be an associate professor in the faculty of medicine and dentistry and enjoys teaching new students. His educational interests include pain and anxiety management for office-based procedures.

Dr. Patricia Zoleta Morales

Dr. Patricia Zoleta Morales was born and raised in the Philippines. She graduated from the University of Manitoba with a Doctor Of Dental Medicine. She worked at our Garden City clinic as a dental assistant for eight years before deciding to become a dentist. Dr. Zoleta is fluent in Filipino (Tagalog) and also has experience volunteering at Siloam Mission as a dental assistant. When sheâs not helping patients, she enjoys travelling with friends and family, watching movies, and spending time with her dog, Bella.

Dr. Lisa Deng

Dr. Lisa Deng began her dental career as a dental hygienist in 2014. After working for four years, she developed a strong interest in restorative dentistry and decided to go back to the University of Manitoba where she received her Doctor of Dental Medicine degree. Dr. Deng enjoys being able to connect with patients and help them with their dental needs. Outside of dentistry, Dr. Deng enjoys spending time with her fiancÃ©, family and friends. Some of her favourite activities include travelling, hot yoga, and trying new restaurants.

Dr. Isabella Sarzynski

Dr. Isabella Sarzynski graduated from the University of Manitoba with a Bachelor of Science and a Doctor of Dental Medicine. Following graduation, she was accepted into the General Practice Residency program at The Schulich School of Medicine & Dentistry where she worked in multiple hospitals in London, Ontario. Now back in Winnipeg, Dr. Sarzynski looks forward to interacting with patients to help them accomplish their dental needs. While not practicing, she enjoys travelling, spending time with friends and family, and reading a good book.
